title: U.S. House Judiciary antitrust report likely to come out as soon as Monday October 5 - source
text: The U.S. House of Representatives Judiciary Committee's antitrust subcommittee is expected to release a much anticipated report into antitrust allegations

title: Facebook names VP of product growth Alex Schultz as new CMO
text: To fill its empty CMO position, Facebook just promoted a longtime Facebook executive focused on product growth to the C-suite. Former VP of product growth and analytics Alex Schultz, who has been with the company since 2007, announced the move Tuesday in a Facebook post.

title: Facebook names Alex Schultz as marketing head
text: Facebook Inc is tapping Alex Schultz, a company veteran who runs product growth, analytics and internationalization at the social media giant, as its new chief marketing officer.

title: Ad exec Martin Sorrell says Facebook and Google shouldn't be broken up, boycotts pointless
text: Famed advertising executive Martin Sorrell told CNBC that Google and Facebook have been exercising more responsibility and shouldn't be broken up by regulators.

title: Pivoting during a pandemic
text: For me, the last six months has shown that people are resilient, and that when faced with a common threat or the need to suddenly rethink everything they might know, we quickly rise to the occasion.

title: Facebook introduces Accounts Center, a tool for managing a growing number of cross-app settings
text: Despite being under antitrust investigations in U.S. and E.U., Facebook today is rolling out a new feature that highlights the extent to which its suite of apps now interoperate.

title: Facebook says it has helped 100,000 people sign up as poll workers
text: Facebook Inc. which finds itself in the pangs of another controversial presidential election that has placed enormous pressure on its platform and how it handles information, on Tuesday said it has helped about 100,000 people sign up as poll workers. Among the highlights, North Carolina election officials said more than 11,000 people signed up from Saturday to Monday morning, according to Facebook.

title: The Compelling Case for Buying the Facebook Stock Dip

title: Philippines accuses Facebook of censoring pro-government content
text: The Philippines accused Facebook on Tuesday of censoring pro-government content which it said was tantamount to curtailing freedom of speech and called for new measures to regulate the social media giant to "level the playing field".
